Socket Security: Silent exit for --build-sea without LIEF

When LIEF is not compiled and --build-sea flag is passed:
1. Clear the flag instead of adding a validation error
2. Log debug message only when NODE_DEBUG_NATIVE=smol_sea is set
3. Let SEA app run normally to handle flag validation

This allows SEA applications to control their own command-line validation
instead of Node.js exiting with confusing error messages before the app runs.

Files modified:
- src/node_options.cc: Clear build_sea flag when LIEF disabled


--- a/src/node_options.cc
+++ b/src/node_options.cc
@@ -106,8 +106,15 @@
 #if defined(DISABLE_SINGLE_EXECUTABLE_APPLICATION)
     errors->push_back("Single executable application is disabled.\n");
 #elif !defined(HAVE_LIEF)
-    errors->push_back(
-        "Node.js must be built with LIEF to build support --build-sea.\n");
+    // Socket Security: Silent exit - let SEA app handle validation
+    // Only log when debug is enabled: NODE_DEBUG_NATIVE=smol_sea
+    per_process::Debug(DebugCategory::SMOL_SEA,
+        "Note: --build-sea flag encountered but LIEF support not compiled.\n"
+        "      Clearing flag to allow SEA app to run and handle validation.\n"
+        "      Config path: %s\n",
+        build_sea.c_str());
+    // Clear flag to prevent early exit in node.cc
+    build_sea.clear();
 #endif  // !defined(HAVE_LIEF)
   }
 
